const __configMetaLoader = async () => {

    //
    // defs
    //
    window.config = {}
    const metaTags = document.querySelectorAll("meta[data-config]")

    //
    // its meta tags
    //
    metaTags.forEach(element => {
        window.config[element.name] = element.content
    });

    //
    // add variables to 
    //
    for (var key in window.config) { 

        //
        // is valid css variable value
        //
        if ( !isValidCSSVariableValue(window.config[key]) ) { continue }

        //
        // set css var 
        //
        setCSSVar(key, window.config[key])
    }



    //
    // validate can be css variable
    //
    function isValidCSSVariableValue(value) {
        const el = document.createElement('div');
        try {
            el.style.setProperty('--test', value);
            // If browser normalized it into empty string, it failed
            return el.style.getPropertyValue('--test') !== '';
        } catch {
            return false;
        }
    }

    //
    // set css variable
    //
    function setCSSVar(name, value, element = document.documentElement) {
        // Prefix with -- if not already
        if (!name.startsWith("--")) {
            name = "--" + name;
        }
        element.style.setProperty(name, value);
    }


}
__configMetaLoader()    </script></head>

                <div>
                    <span class="main-text">
                        Clear the clutter, clear your mind. Well handle the heavy lifting.
                    </span>
                </div>
                <script>
                    window.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", ()=>{
                        
                        // feature words
                        const featureWords = [
                            "clutter,",
                            "mind.",
                        ]
                        const isFeature = (word) => {
                            for (var k in featureWords) {
                                if (featureWords[k] == word.innerHTML) {
                                    return true
                                }; 
                            }
                            return false
                        }

                        // get words 
                        const {words} = anime.splitText(".main-text", { chars: true });
                        let offset = 0

                        // iter words
                        for (var wordkey in words) { const word = words[wordkey]

                            // get chars 
                            const chars = Array.from(word.children)

                            // iter chars
                            for (var key in chars) { const char = chars[key]

                                // add letter offset
                                offset = offset + 1

                                // set starting opacity
                                char.style.opacity = "0.1"
                                
                                // timeline add
                                window.context.timeline.add(char, {
                                    opacity:1,
                                    duration: 70,
                                }, offset);

                                // check special adds
                                if (char.innerHTML === "," || char.innerHTML === ".") offset = offset + 15
                            }

                        }

                    })
                </script>
            </div>
        </div>

    <script data-src="text-measure.js">
let textMeasureStylesApplied = false
function appendTextMeasureStyles() {

    if (textMeasureStylesApplied) return
    textMeasureStylesApplied = true

    const style = document.createElement('style');
    style.textContent = `
        .text-measure-container {
            top:0px;
            left:0px;
            width:100%;
            height:100%;
            text-wrap: nowrap;
            display:flex;
            align-items:center;
            justify-content:center;
        }
    `;

    document.head.appendChild(style);
}
appendTextMeasureStyles();

function textMeasure(container, target) {

    //
    // inner ele / span
    //
    const pad = 10
    const targetWidth = parseInt(container.offsetWidth) - pad * 2

    //
    // set starting font size
    //
    target.style.fontSize = "6px"

    //
    // iter defs 
    //
    const diff = () => { return targetWidth - parseInt(target.offsetWidth) }
    const targetDiff = pad * 2

    //
    // iter size up 
    //
    for (let i = 0; i < 100; i++) {

        //
        // eval  
        //
        if ( diff() <= targetDiff ) { break } 

        //
        // set font size    
        //
        target.style.fontSize = ( parseInt(target.style.fontSize) + 2 ).toString() + "px"

        // report max
        if (i > 98) {
            return console.error("text measure iteration error maxed out, check count"); break;
        }
    }

    //
    // eval style, center text-measure-container (container) if needed
    //
    if (container.style.width===undefined) return
    container.style.left = ( ( 100 - parseInt(container.style.width) ) / 2 ).toString() + "%"
    
}

window.addEventListener("load", function () {
    
    const targets = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll(".text-measure-container"))

    for (var key in targets) {

        const container = targets[key]
        const child = container.querySelector(".text-measure")
        
        if (child===null) {
            console.log("text-measure requires parent with .text-measure-target and child .text-measure-span ")
            return 
        }

        textMeasure(container, child)
    }
    
});</script>
    <script data-src="000_context.js">

//
// window context
//
window.context = {
    ...window.config,
    preview:Boolean((new URLSearchParams(window.location.search)).get("preview")),
    qsFrame:(new URLSearchParams(window.location.search)).get("frame"),
    write:(new URLSearchParams(window.location.search)).get("write"),
}

//
// frame range 
//
window.context.frameRange = (tarOrFrom, dur) => {
    const from = tarOrFrom * window.context.durationInFrames
    if (dur===undefined) return from
    const duration = dur * window.context.durationInFrames
    return [from, duration]
}

//
// add functions to run on frame update
//
const onFrame = []
window.context.onFrame = (fn) => { 
    onFrame.push(fn)
    if (window.context.frame!==undefined) fn(window.context.frame) // ensures first update (sometimes the frame is set before the functions are addded, this is needed)
}
let first = true
window.context.setFrame = (frame) =>{

    //
    // validate 
    //
    if (frame===undefined) return 

    //
    // check current frame
    //
    if (!first && frame===window.context.frame) return
    first = false
    console.log('new frame', frame)
    //
    // set frame
    //
    window.context.frame = frame
    for (var key in onFrame) {
        onFrame[key](frame)
    }

}


//
// load
//
window.addEventListener("load", () => {
    if (window.context.frame==null) return
    window.context.setFrame(parseInt(window.context.frame))
})



//
//
//
//
// timeline
// timeline
// timeline
// timeline
//
//
//
//


const { animate, createTimeline } = anime

//
// create window timeline
//
window.context.timeline = createTimeline({ autoplay:false })
window.context.timelineTarget = {}

//
// add whole timeline anim (baseline anim / placeholder anim to fill timeline)
//
const anim = animate(window.timelineTarget, {
    duration:window.context.durationInFrames,
    number:[0,1],
})

//
// sync
//
window.context.timeline.sync(anim, 0)
window.context.onFrame((frame)=> {
    window.context.timeline.seek(frame)
})
</script>
    <script data-src="printer3.js">const LoadPrinter3 = () => {

	const { stagger } = anime;

	const makeID = () => "printer-three-id" + Math.random().toString().replaceAll(".", "");

	const makeSpace = () => {
		const spacer = document.createElement("div");
		spacer.id = "printer-3-space-" + makeID();
		spacer.className = "printer3-space";
		spacer.innerHTML = `<span>i</span>`;
		spacer.style.opacity = 0;
		spacer.style.display = "inline-block";
		return spacer;
	};

	const makeSpan = (char) => {
		const span = document.createElement("span");
		span.id = makeID();
		span.className = "char";
		span.textContent = char;
		span.style.opacity = 0;
		return span;
	};

  	const makeWord = (word) => {
		const wordEl = document.createElement("div");
		wordEl.style.display = "inline-block";
		wordEl.className = "words";

		for (let key in word) {
			const char = word[key];
			const span = makeSpan(char);
			wordEl.appendChild(span);
		}
		return wordEl;
  	};


    //
    // init printer 
    //
  	function initPrinterThree(targetElement) {
		if (!targetElement) return;

		//
		// get text
		//
		const text = targetElement.getAttribute("data-text");
		if (!text) {
			console.log("printer3.js target was found without attr: data-text (must have)")
			return;
		}

		// clear original content
		targetElement.innerHTML = "";

		// split into words
		const words = text.split(" ");

		for (let w = 0; w < words.length; w++) {
			const wordEl = makeWord(words[w]);
			targetElement.appendChild(wordEl);

			// add space if not last
			if (w + 1 !== words.length) {
				const lastSpace = makeSpace();
				wordEl.appendChild(lastSpace);
			}
		}

		// Animation setup
		const frameStart = eval(targetElement.getAttribute("data-frame-start") || "0");
		const duration = eval(targetElement.getAttribute("data-duration") || "1000");
		const stag = targetElement.getAttribute("data-stagger");
		const delay = stagger(stag != null ? stag : 3);

		const children = Array.from(targetElement.querySelectorAll("span.char"));

		//
		// window timeline add
		//
		window.context.timeline.add(children,
			{
				opacity: 1,
				duration,
				delay,
			},
			frameStart
		);
	}

    //
    // init printers 
    //
    document.querySelectorAll("div[data-printer-three]").forEach((el) => {
        initPrinterThree(el);
    });

}

LoadPrinter3()</script>

    <script type="text/javascript">

        const paths = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.title-lower-svg path'))
        paths.push(...Array.from(document.querySelectorAll(".title-upper-svg path")))
        
        for (var key in paths) {

            const path = paths[key]
            const len = path.getTotalLength()
            path.style.strokeDashoffset = len
            path.style.strokeDasharray = len
            
            const start = 100 + ( parseInt(key) * 15 )

            window.context.timeline.add(path, {
                strokeDashoffset:0,
                easing: 'inOut',
                duration: 200,
            }, start);
        }
    </script>
